<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-05-0218 </DOCNO><TEXT>The state of direct utilization of geothermy in the southern part of stateof New Mexico and New Mexico State University was researched. In Animasin the southern part of the state, geothermal water has been utilizedfor the cultivation of roses in greenhouses, and this business has beencommercialized. New Mexico State University has taken geothermal waterin its premises, and utilized it as the heat source for large scale greenhousesas well as the room heating for the facilities in its premises. In thegeneral meeting of Geothermal Resources Council USA, the number of paperspresented was fewer than before, and there was not any report on newproject. In the inspection tour of the general meeting, the wind powergeneration facilities of about 4,000 windmills at San Gorgonio pass andthe two-stage flash geothermal power plant and the binary geothermalpower plant in Imperial Valley were inspected.(4 refs, 7 figs, 3 tabs,8 photos)</TEXT></DOC>